track_notes: I parked in front of Dollar Tree at Thunderbird and 7th because the parking area at the end of Central (12800 N Central Ave) was full, and also closed at 7pm.  This made the hike a little longer. The UP track includes an extra half mile or so because I forgot my flashlight and returned to the car for that.  Trail is easy but rocky, and the way up is on a very steep 4wd road which is popular with hikers (its very busy).
The mileage of this track is round-trip. Start from the trailhead off Central Ave which has a parking lot with about 30 spaces.  12898 North Central Ave, Phoenix AZ, 85022
track_title: Shaw Butte up and back from Central Ave trailhead

track_notes: There is a nice trailhead with plenty of parking at the end of 7th street (gpx coordinates 33.5856, -112.0823 as noted on K7AHR writeup for this summit).  This route is steeper trail on the way up and meets up with the road near the top, and then takes the road down and loops back between Shaw Butte and North Mountain, W7A/AW-060.  You could add North Mountain to the route to make it a double.
track_title: Shaw Butte loop hike via Shaw Butte Trail 306
